<#
.SYNOPSIS
    This PowerShell script ensures that the Account Lockout Duration is configured to a minimum of 15 minutes, in compliance with STIG WN10-AC-000005.

.NOTES
    Author          : Jonathan Gistand
    LinkedIn        : https://linkedin.com/in/jgdev/
    GitHub          : https://github.com/jgdev-arc
    Date Created    : 2025-06-02
    Last Modified   : 2025-06-02
    Version         : 1.0
    CVEs            : N/A
    Plugin IDs      : N/A
    STIG-ID         : WN10-AC-000005
#>

# Set Account Lockout Duration to 15 minutes using secedit

$infContent = @"
[Unicode]
Unicode=yes
[System Access]
LockoutDuration = 15
[Version]
signature="\$CHICAGO\$"
Revision=1
"@

# Write .inf file to temporary location
$infPath = "$env:TEMP\V-220002-lockout-duration.inf"
$infContent | Set-Content -Path $infPath -Encoding Unicode

# Apply the configuration
secedit /configure /db secedit.sdb /cfg $infPath /quiet

# Confirm success
Start-Sleep -Seconds 2
Write-Output "‚úÖ Account lockout duration has been set to 15 minutes. (STIG: WN10-AC-000005)"


<#
README

# STIG: WN10-AC-000005 - Configure Account Lockout Duration

## üîê Overview

This STIG requires that **Windows 10 systems** enforce an **Account Lockout Duration** of **at least 15 minutes** to reduce the effectiveness of brute force login attempts.

- **STIG ID:** WN10-AC-000005  
- **Rule Title:** Account lockout duration must be configured to 15 minutes or greater  
- **Severity:** Medium  
- **Fix Text:** Set the policy at:
  
  `Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Account Policies >> Account Lockout Policy >> "Account lockout duration"`  
  to **15 minutes or greater**. A setting of `0` (manual unlock by admin) is also acceptable.

## ‚öôÔ∏è What This Script Does

This PowerShell script:
- Creates a `.inf` security template file
- Sets `LockoutDuration = 15`
- Applies it using `secedit`

